uint not defined...
should add something like

typedef unsigned int uint;

OK, the problem seems to occur at comboreduct/table/table.cc line 326:

```
    interpreter_visitor iv(tr);
    auto ai = boost::apply_visitor(iv);
    for (const multi_type_seq& vs : itable)
        push_back(ai(vs.get_variant()));
```

The vs.get_variant fails to notice that the output type is an enum, not a double, and causes the wrong interpreter_visitor signature to be used:  viz, it incorrectly calls  vertex operator()(const std::vector<contin_t>& inputs) instead of vertex operator()(const std::vector<vertex>& inputs) 

Perhaps this wouldn't be so bad, if we could still call mixed_interpreter on double inputs, but that seems to fail because of how the interpreter .. hmmm. wait. maybe I see a solution ..

