I'm bisecting ... below is a note-to-self.

Code in this branch crashes unless the following patch is applied:

--- a/opencog/learning/moses/metapopulation/deme_expander.cc
+++ b/opencog/learning/moses/metapopulation/deme_expander.cc
@@ -124,6 +124,7 @@ bool deme_expander::create_demes(const combo_tree& exemplar)
                                "non-selected features");
                 // Insert exemplar features as they are not pruned
                 sf.second.insert(xmplr_features.begin(), xmplr_features.end());
+xmplr_seq.push_back(exemplar);
             }

```
         // add the complement of the selected features to ignore_ops
```

A much simpler way to do this is to just say

logger().fine() << "get_candidate before reduct: " << tr;

You don't need the stringstream gunk

The argument I added to CYTHON_ADD_MODULE_PYX is:

 -I ${PROJECT_BINARY_DIR}

to tell it to look in the build directory.

