I was thinking about that too. Yes it would work. However, I was reading some information on recommended JSON REST API responses, for example this one, that suggest this approach:

http://jsonapi.org/format/

```
Singular Resources

Singular resources are represented as JSON objects. However, they are still wrapped inside an array:

{
  "posts": [{
    // an individual post document
  }]
}
```

@jadeoneill @AmeBel Using atomspace.print_list() is a good idea, but first that would require modifying the binding, because right now it would just print to stdout:
https://github.com/opencog/opencog/blob/master/opencog/cython/opencog/atomspace.pxd#L153
https://github.com/opencog/opencog/blob/master/opencog/atomspace/AtomSpace.h#L114

